title: More About Me
description: I guess this contains other personal information about me if you're trying to impersonate me. I'm generally a very boring person, so I'm not sure why someone would want to impersonate me other than for fraud.

sections.content: None.
Graduated from the University of Washington Bothell in June 2022 with a double major in Computer Science and Mathematics.
Unemployed since.

This section ranks the programming languages I'm familar with on a scale of 1 to 5. 1 Being I can use it, but don't expect me to have any keywords or style memorized. 5 being okayish intermediate if you give me an hour to cram before the interview. 3 is if I was really good at it, but i forgot a few of the major classes and keyword names or that Python is messing up my syntax. 0 is if there are some road blocks to me learning it, but an attempt has been made.
Java - 3
I used it in high school and first year of college, so about 2 years, but there is a large gap afterwards till my distributed computing class.
JavaScript - 4
I don't train in this language for interviews, but if you want me to make a webpage I'm confident in it. I just need to refresh myself once in a while on keywords and class names.
Python - 5
I practice leetcode in this language, but not creating classes.
MATLAB - 3
Used it for a signal computing class and numerical anaylysis class series. I'm confident in it, but I'll need to see some code before I have to use it again.
Used this for a statistics class. Learned nothing from it. Can use it, but I'm pretty useless at this language.
I love the idea of the language, hate the project setup and compiling process. It sucks. Used this for data structures and algorithm for a year in college. Hasn't touched it since.
